    "abstractNote": "An Arabic inscription from the Islamic period, recently discovered on a rock on the outskirts of Najr\u0101n, is engraved vertically. The author, who asks God to forgive his sins, is Christian, as evidenced by his Syriac name, the formulas and the presence of a cross (plus a second cross, apparently added at a later date). We might add that he was probably of Syriac culture, because in the Near East, vertical inscriptions are found only in this script. The palaeography implies a date after 800 ad, perhaps around 900-1000 ad.",
